{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InvertedPendulum"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["Linux"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Description","level":3,"text":"Description"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This environment is the cartpole environment based on the work done by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Barto, Sutton, and Anderson in ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ieeexplore.ieee.org\/document\/6313077","isActive":true},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"just like in the classic environments but now powered by the Mujoco physics simulator -","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allowing for more complex experiments (such as varying the effects of gravity).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This environment involves a cart that can moved linearly, with a pole fixed on it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at one end and having another end free. The cart can be pushed left or right, and the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"goal is to balance the pole on the top of the cart by applying forces on the cart.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Action-Space","level":3,"text":"Action Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The agent take a 1-element vector for actions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The action space is a continuous ","type":"text"},{"code":"(action)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"code":"[-3, 3]","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", where ","type":"text"},{"code":"action","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the numerical force applied to the cart (with magnitude representing the amount of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"force and sign representing the direction)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Max","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Joint","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Force applied on the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Force (N)","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Observation-Space","level":3,"text":"Observation Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The state space consists of positional values of different body parts of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pendulum system, followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with all the positions ordered before all the velocities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The observation is a "},{"code":"ndarray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with shape "},{"code":"(4,)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" where the elements correspond to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Observation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Max","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"position of the cart along the linear surface","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"position (m)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"1","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"vertical angle of the pole on the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angle (rad)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"2","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"linear velocity of the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"velocity (m\/s)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angular velocity of the pole on the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"anglular velocity (rad\/s)","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Rewards","level":3,"text":"Rewards"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The goal is to make the inverted pendulum stand upright (within a certain angle limit)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as long as possible - as such a reward of +1 is awarded for each timestep that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the pole is upright.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Starting-State","level":3,"text":"Starting State"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All observations start in state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0) with a uniform noise in the range","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of [-0.01, 0.01] added to the values for stochasticity.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Episode-End","level":3,"text":"Episode End"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The episode ends when any of the following happens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Truncation: The episode duration reaches 1000 timesteps."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: Any of the state space values is no longer finite."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: The absolutely value of the vertical angle between the pole and the cart is greater than 0.2 radian."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Arguments","level":3,"text":"Arguments"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No additional arguments are currently supported.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["env = gym.make('InvertedPendulum-v4')"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is no v3 for InvertedPendulum, unlike the robot environments where a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"v3 and beyond take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Version-History","level":3,"text":"Version History"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks (including inverted pendulum)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"]]},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Gym"}],"roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"s:3Gy